{"questionId":"21448","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A garden has a triangular sunshade suspended from three points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>B</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, relative to an origin in the corner of the garden. All distances are measured&nbsp;in metres.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mtext>CA</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>×</mo><mover><mtext>CB</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mtext>CA</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>×</mo><mover><mtext>CB</mtext><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>24</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>(M1) </strong></em>if less than 2 entries are correct.</p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21448","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.5b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find CA→×CB→.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.10—Vector definitions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}